$ Perl function: mkdir

Perl's mdkir won't create nested (sub-)directories (as a shell's → Linux/shell/commands/mkdir without the `-p` option).
-
To create nested subdirectories, use the → development/languages/Perl/modules[Perl module] 
→ development/languages/Perl/modules/File/Path[File::Path] (function `make_path`):

gh|about-perl|/functions/mkdir.pl|one-to-one|

sa:

  → development/languages/Perl/functions/index 
